Link is coloring a triforce, which consists of four equilateral triangles and is depicted below. He has three colors to use: gold, black, and green. So that it remains recognizable, he doesn't want to color any two triangles the same color if they share a side. How many different ways can he color the triforce? (Two colorings that differ by rotation are considered distinct.) [asy]
size(50);
draw((0,0)--(2,0)--(1,1.732)--cycle);
draw((1,0)--(1.5,.866)--(.5,.866)--cycle);
[/asy]

Congruent segments are used to form equilateral triangles in this sequence so that each figure contains one more triangle than the preceding figure. Figure 3 of the sequence is made with seven congruent segments. How many congruent segments must be used to make Figure 25 of the sequence?

[asy]
draw((0,0)--(10,0)--(5,8.7)--cycle);
draw((15,0)--(25,0)--(30,8.7)--(20,8.7)--cycle);
draw((20,8.7)--(25,0));
draw((35,0)--(55,0)--(50,8.7)--(40,8.7)--cycle);
draw((40,8.7)--(45,0)--(50,8.7));
draw((60,0)--(80,0)--(85,8.7)--(65,8.7)--cycle);
draw((65,8.7)--(70,0)--(75,8.7)--(80,0));
label("Figure 1",(2,0),S);
label("Figure 2",(20,-10),S);
label("Figure 3",(45,0),S);
label("Figure 4",(76,-10),S);
[/asy]

There are nine unit triangles in the three rows of this triangle. If you add three more rows to the bottom of this triangle so that each row has 2 more unit triangles than the previous row, how many unit triangles will there be?

[asy]
draw((0,0)--(15,26)--(30,0)--cycle);
draw((5,8.7)--(10,0)--(20,17.3));
draw((20,0)--(25,8.7)--(5,8.7));
draw((20,0)--(10,17.3)--(20,17.3));
[/asy]

Fourteen white cubes are put together to form the figure on the right.  The complete surface of the figure, including the bottom, is painted red.  The figure is then separated into individual cubes.  How many of the individual cubes have exactly four red faces?

[asy]
size(150);
pair a=(1,0),b=(0,1),c=(0.45,0.4);

void drawcube(pair loc){
     filldraw(loc+b--loc--loc+a--loc+a+c--loc+a+b+c--loc+b+c--cycle,white);
     draw(loc+b--loc+a+b--loc+a+b+c^^loc+a+b--loc+a);
}

pair location[]={origin,b,a,2a,3a,3a+b,-c,3a-c,-2c,-2c+b,-2c+a,-2c+2a,-2c+3a,-2c+3a+b};

for(int i; i<14;++i){
   drawcube(location[i]);
}


[/asy]

