What is the shortest distance that can be travelled if you start at any point, $A$, $B$, $C$, or $D$, and visit the other three points once?

[asy]
pair A,B,C, D;
A = (-3,3); B = (3,0); C = (0, -4); D = (0,0);
draw(D--B--C--cycle); draw(D--A--B--cycle);draw(D--A--C--cycle);
label("$A$", A, NW);label("$B$", B, E); label("$C$", C, S);label("$D$", D, NE);
label("3", D--B, S); label("6", A--B, NE); label("6", A--C, SW); label("4", D--C, NW+N);
label("5", A--D, SE+NE); label("5", C--B, E);
[/asy]

The figure below represents a figure with a total of 120 triangles and $n$ points labeled as vertices on the horizontal base. What is the value of $n$?

[asy]size(250,400);
pair P = (3,4);
real r = .05;
draw((0,0)--P); draw((1,0)--P); draw((3,0)--P); draw((4.5,0)--P); draw((7,0)--P); draw((7,0)--(8,0)); fill(circle((8+3r,0),r)); fill(circle((8+7r,0),r)); draw((8+15r,0)--(9+15r,0)); draw((9+15r,0)--P); draw((11+15r,0)--P); fill(circle((8+11r,0),r)); draw((0,0)--(7,0)); draw((9+15r,0)--(11+15r,0));
label("$P$",P,N); label("$A_1$",(0,0),S); label("$A_2$",(1,0),S); label("$A_3$",(3,0),S); label("$A_4$",(4.5,0),S); label("$A_5$",(7,0),S); label("$A_{n-1}$",(9+15r,0),S); label("$A_n$",(11+15r,0),S);[/asy]

